'''Islam in [[Tonga]]''' is a small minority religion in the country. Muslims in Tonga belong to [[Sunni Islam|Sunni]] denomination. The number of Muslims was estimated at less than 1000 in 2010 by the [[Pew Research Center]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pewforum.org/2011/01/27/table-muslim-population-by-country/|title=Table: Muslim Population by Country|publisher=Pew Research Center|date=27 January 2011|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref> in a [[demographics of Tonga|population]] of about 108,000, while a report by the Fiji Muslim League estimated that in 2002 there were about 70 Muslim Tongan nationals out of a Muslim population of 100.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/stream/FijiMuslimLeagueSituationReportTongaSamoa/FmlSituationReport-tongaSamoa2002#page/n5/mode/2up|title=Fiji Muslim League situation report: Tonga and Samoa|date=5 July 2002|work=Fiji Muslim League|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref>
==Muslim school== [[Tonga]]’s [[Muslim]] community is planning to raise funds in the [[Middle East]] to build a new boarding school on Tongatapu.<ref name="RNZI_31714">{{cite news |url=http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=31714 |title=Plans for a Muslim school in Tonga |date=24 April 2007 |work=[[Radio New Zealand International]] |accessdate=5 October 2011}}</ref> The school is to follow the Tongan school curriculum, but additionally offer the [[Arabic]] language and Islamic studies as options. Sheikh Imam Abdul Fader, a spiritual leader of the Tongan Muslim community and a mathematics teacher, said their project is to build a three-story boarding school that will serve [[Muslims]] and non-Muslims, especially orphans who are often deprived of [[education]]. The [[children]] in the school will not be forced to study or convert to [[Islam]]. He also said that a small delegation of Tongan Muslims will leave in June 2007 for [[Saudi Arabia]] and [[Qatar]] to seek donations and funding for the new school, since these two countries are well known for their strong contributions to the Muslim community in Australia and New Zealand.
